channel.description: The latest CVEs for Norton -- all products

item.title: CVE-2019-9695|2024-08-04T21:54:45.143Z -- norton -- norton%20core
item.description: Norton Core prior to v278 may be susceptible to an arbitrary code execution issue, which is a type of vulnerability that has the potential of allowing an individual to execute arbitrary commands or code on a target machine or in a target process. Note that this exploit is only possible with direct physical access to the device.

item.title: CVE-2019-9700|2024-08-04T21:54:45.471Z -- norton -- norton%20password%20manager
item.description: Norton Password Manager, prior to 6.3.0.2082, may be susceptible to an address spoofing issue. This type of issue may allow an attacker to disguise their origin IP address in order to obfuscate the source of network traffic.
